# Copilot custom instructions (MemForge)

This file is the per-repo Copilot Chat instruction surface. Copilot inlines its content into every chat request when `github.copilot.chat.codeGeneration.useInstructionFiles` is enabled.

## Memory context

The operator maintains persistent memory in MemForge folders. Treat the following as session-start context: identity, accumulated feedback, ongoing project state, references to external systems.

Read these files at session start:

- `~/.claude/global-memory/MEMORY.md`
- `~/.claude/projects/PER_CWD_WORKSPACE_NAME/memory/MEMORY.md`

(Replace `PER_CWD_WORKSPACE_NAME` with your actual workspace folder name. Run `ls ~/.claude/projects/` to find it.)

When the operator references a memory by title, follow the link in `MEMORY.md` to read the underlying file before answering.

When the operator asks you to remember something cross-session, write it as a new file in the appropriate memory folder using the v0.3.0 frontmatter schema (see `~/claude-projects/memforge/spec/SPEC.md`). The filesystem watcher (memforge `memory-watch`) will commit the file automatically.

## MemForge tools available on PATH

You can invoke these directly when the operator asks for memory operations:

- `memory-audit-deep --strict` — verify memory integrity (UID uniqueness, taxonomy compliance, supersedes resolution, broken links, rollup staleness).
- `memory-query --topic <X> --type <Y>` — find memories by frontmatter.
- `memory-cluster-suggest` — surface candidate rollup clusters.
- `memory-rollup create --slug <name> <files>` — pull files into a topic subfolder + generate README parent.
- `memory-dlp-scan --staged --strict` — pre-commit scan for credentials / secrets / PII.
- `memory-audit-log verify` — validate the tamper-evident audit chain.

## Sensitivity

The memory folder may contain entries with `sensitivity: restricted` or `sensitivity: privileged`. Honor those classifications:

- Do not include privileged content in code comments, commit messages, or PR descriptions.
- Do not echo privileged content back to the operator in chat unless the operator explicitly asks for it.
- For Copilot suggestions: privileged content should not influence suggestions visible in shared / pair-programming sessions.
